freebsd-snapshot-upgrade

Instructions on performing upgrade using FreeBSD snapshots:

1. Download recent snapshot, optionally specifying version:
# freebsd-snapshot-upgrade
or
# freebsd-snapshot-upgrade 9.1-STABLE

Utility will create installation script under /tmp, e.g.
/tmp/freebsd-snapshot-9.1-STABLE/snapshot-install

2. Boot into single user and install new snapshot:
# shutdown now
# /tmp/freebsd-snapshot-XXX/snapshot-install

3. Merge configuration. New snapshot /etc is available under
/tmp/freebsd-snapshot-XXX/etc
